    <note type="translation" xml:lang="en">Ādam b. Saʿd b. ʿĪsā, originally al-Kīlānī, then al-Makkī.
He resided in Mecca for nearly twenty years and married there, and in his later years, he lived in Ribāṭ Sukkar. He was a trusted person.
He died in Dhū al-Qaʿda in the year 867 AH.</note>
